#X text 17 251 Attack chords mix;
#X text 466 85 This module combines the sine \, sawtooth \, and square
wave chords.;
#X text 442 130 It allows each grouping to be influenced by a different
axis of the accelerometer \, by connecting each to one of the expanded
signals from each of the accelerometer axes.;
#X text 496 186 This results in a fluid sound \, with natural nuances
resulting from different hand movements.;
#X text 442 231 Most importantly \, the controls have been carefully
tweaked so that a flat hand 'wobble' has a clear \, direct response
in the sound of the chords.;
#X text 448 287 New chords are triggered by claps \, as detected by
the 'clap detector' module. When a clap occurs \, this module responds
first with a 'chord attack' \, then a 'chord sustain'.;
#X text 466 343 The reason for breaking the sound into two parts was
to ensure that only the sustained tail of the chord was affected by
the expanded signals from the accelerometer.;
#X text 448 399 Before breaking the sound into two parts \, the accelerometer
signals would clash with the onset of the chord \, causing a 'popping'
sound. This new module eliminates that problem.;
#X text 442 455 Finally \, the combined and filtered waves are mixed
together. The final mix is split into two signals \, with one signal
going through a delay line \, to create a 'phase' effect and thicken
the sound of the chords.;
